intro:
  eyebrow: "About"
  heading: "Professional Psychotherapy and Counselling in London"
  text: "Philippe Jacquet holds a Doctorate in Professional Studies from the University of Essex, with a unique clinical and research focus on eating disorders in male populations. He is widely recognised as one of the most distinctively qualified practitioners in the UK working at this intersection of Jungian psychology and disordered eating. Our Central London and Harley Street team takes a holistic, person-centred approach to mental health. Rather than applying a fixed protocol, each therapist works collaboratively with clients to design an authentic treatment plan — one that may draw on psychotherapy, counselling, art therapy, hypnotherapy, or depth-psychological methods depending on what is most helpful. We work with eating disorders (including anorexia, bulimia, binge eating disorder, and ARFID); addiction (alcohol, drugs, gambling, sex addiction, and behavioural compulsions); trauma and PTSD including complex developmental trauma; anxiety, depression, and burnout; relationship difficulties and attachment challenges; life transition, identity, meaning, and midlife; and male-specific presentations including body image, disordered eating, and emotional avoidance. Every member of the team holds full professional accreditation. We are recognised by major private health insurers including Bupa, AXA Health, Vitality, and Cigna. Evening and weekend appointments are available across all locations for those requiring discretion."
  quote: "The most difficult thing in life is to know yourself. — Thales"
